14:
What do you mean what? Idols
need managers! Their careers
depend on it!
22: Sure, call it whatever you want!
27:
Thanks to Dia's help, our music is
good to go. But we're still lacking in
other areas.
33: Come on, Mr. Producer! Help us out!
38:
Wait, who died and made me
producer?
42: Who cares? It's your lucky day.
44:
I don't even know what a producer
does!
49:
I thought that'd be obvious. You'll be
responsible for looking after Noenne.
52: Isn't making all of her meals enough?
53:
I mean, if there's something I can do
to help, I don't mind, but...
58:
Really?! Then it's official! Thank you,
Mr. Producer!
64:
All right, it's our first official meeting
as Hard Rock Magic.
73:
Everyone please take a look at the
agenda in front of you.
77:
Starting from HRM'S goals... Number
one: Return home. Number two:
Grow as idols.
80:
About goal number one... Any
developments, Stella?
84:
Currently we have located six
worlds. However, none of the areas
in question lead to Noenne's
homeworld.
86:
I suspect we will only be able to
achieve our first goal once I have
completed my starchart.
90:
Then we'll have to get Light home
first. Let's get that out of the way
ASAP.
96:
Have I become no more than a side
quest?!
99:
Right, well, I guess that means we
should prioritize our growth as idols.
Lessons will be important, but...
103:
Maybe we should focus on the spirit
of the band first.
109: Spirit? Don't they have plenty of that?
114: La la la, rah rah la!
122:
It's okay! I won't let them wreck the
stage or anything!
126: Alk... Just what has possessed you?
128:
Your group has a talent for getting
into trouble but...
130:
This time, I worry you're in over your
heads. What was the name of that
competition? BRASS?
134:
Yes. It stands for Battle Royale: All
Star Smash.
138:
How curious that the history of such
a distant world would so closely
resemble our zodiac legends...
142:
If my conjectures are on the money,
SHE could be dangerous...
148: Good evening. May we chat for a bit?
153:
Good evening. What may I do for
you?
156:
I would like to know why you haven't
moved on yet.
159:
You see, there's a legend that's
rather famous on this world. A
pitiable tale of a rat tricking a cat
from entering the zodiac pantheon.
163:
And according to Kapipi, your feline
country used to be one of the
thirteen warring kingdoms.
177:
Don't push her around! 
DON'T BULLY MY CATHERINE!
181: But this person speaks the truth.
183:
In our world, the legends are the
same. The cat kingdom was duped
by Littleton, and we lost everything. I
was the last to compete...
186: The last to fail, at becoming an idol...
188:
Thus I haunted the mice, to garner
revenge for—
200:
Look here! You're my band mate!
Nothing's going to change that!
202:
We've been together forever!
Smiling, laughing, losing! We've
done it all!
206:
But we're just getting started
making magic together! It's even in
our group name!
211:
*Sniff, sniff* Well said! 
You're one of us, Catherine!
218:
Sometimes, just sometimes, the
heart is a truer guide than the mind.
223:
Then may I stay in the group with
you, Noenne?
235: You, you can stay with me too!
250:
Waaaaah! We're going to be the
best idols! I promise, promise,
promise you!
